A trick is completed when a card from each hand has been place (and displayed) face up in the "Cards for current trick" container.  The cards are selected one from each "Hand" starting with "Declarer" (for this version) and going around "the square" to "West Opponent" then "Dummy" and finally "East Opponent".  The time each trick is displayed in the "Cards for current trick" is determined by another player entered field "Time a trick is displayed" in seconds.  Please add this entry field under "How many tricks between each memory challenge".  When the display time has been reached, a new trick is created in the same way.  When the "How many tricks between each memory challenge" has been reached, the creation of tricks stops and a message pops up for the player to guess the cards that were in the tricks to that point.  Add another button "Start the next set up tricks" which when clicked starts the tricks being formed for the next round.  The game stops when all cards have been used.  As each trick is formed by displaying the chosen card from each "Hand", the card is removed from the "Hand" it came from.  The player guesses the cards in the tricks to that point in the game by clicking on a card in "All Possible Cards".  If the card clicked in "All Possible Cards" was in one of the tricks in the current set then a message is displayed "Correct" otherwise  an "Incorrect" message is displayed and the Incorrect counter is incremented by 1.  Each click of a card in "All Possible Cards" increments the "Attempted" counter.